{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567401","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567401"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T00:01:02+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T00:01:02+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18970"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18970","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18970"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.14,0.23,0.07,0.1,0.46]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11704"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"105830"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11704","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11704"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question","status":"accepted","createdAt":"2025-01-21T20:14:09+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-14T09:56:53+09:30","updatedAction":"revised","acceptedAt":"2025-01-21T20:34:42+10:30","editorNotifiedAt":null,"feedbackAt":"2025-09-25 16:38:26"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18970"}},"updatedBy":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"9435"}},"author":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"16151"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88299"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"6"},{"type":"tags","id":"28"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"1491"},{"type":"tags","id":"1675"},{"type":"tags","id":"2779"},{"type":"tags","id":"3077"},{"type":"tags","id":"4977"},{"type":"tags","id":"4979"},{"type":"tags","id":"6275"},{"type":"tags","id":"11626"},{"type":"tags","id":"11639"},{"type":"tags","id":"11676"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27536"},{"type":"contributions","id":"30003"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43714"}]},"lastContribution":{"data":null},"lastRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88299"}},"lastActivity":{"data":null},"lastFeedback":{"data":null}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"105830","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/105830"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAn 81-year-old woman is admitted to hospital with worsening bone pain from metastatic breast cancer. She has a medical history of Parkinson disease, atrial fibrillation, hypertension, and osteoporosis. Her regular medications include levodopa/carbidopa, domperidone, sertraline, ramipril, bisoprolol, apixaban and denosumab. She reports increasing dizziness on standing over the past two weeks, which has led to two falls.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears comfortable at rest. Her pulse rate is 68/min and blood pressure 142/85 mmHg while supine. On standing, her pulse rate increases to 85/min and blood pressure drops to 95/60 mmHg. She has a mild resting tremor of her right hand and reduced facial expression. She has generalised reduced muscle bulk but normal tone.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENon-pharmacological measures including compression stockings and increased fluid intake have not improved her symptoms.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate pharmacological treatment for her orthostatic hypotension?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Pyridostigmine","Midodrine","Droxidopa","Ephedrine","Fludrocortisone"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with symptomatic orthostatic hypotension in the context of Parkinson disease and multiple comorbidities. The significant drop in blood pressure upon standing (\u0026gt;20 mmHg systolic) confirms the diagnosis. Given that non-pharmacological measures have been unsuccessful and she has had recurrent falls, pharmacological therapy is indicated.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFludrocortisone\u003C/strong\u003E is the most appropriate first-line pharmacological treatment. It is a synthetic mineralocorticoid that increases plasma volume through sodium retention. It has good evidence for efficacy in neurogenic orthostatic hypotension and is generally well-tolerated. The main side effects include hypokalaemia and ankle swelling, which can be monitored and managed.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMidodrine\u003C/strong\u003E is a selective alpha-1 adrenergic agonist that increases peripheral vascular resistance. While effective, it can worsen supine hypertension, which is particularly concerning given this patient\u0027s baseline hypertension and Parkinson disease.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPyridostigmine\u003C/strong\u003E is an acetylcholinesterase inhibitor that can be useful in treating orthostatic hypotension, particularly in patients with autonomic failure. However, it has less evidence for efficacy compared to fludrocortisone and may worsen tremor in Parkinson disease.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDroxidopa\u003C/strong\u003E is a synthetic precursor of norepinephrine that can be effective in neurogenic orthostatic hypotension. However, it is generally reserved as a second-line agent due to cost and limited availability.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEphedrine\u003C/strong\u003E is a non-selective adrenergic agonist that can improve orthostatic hypotension. However, its use is limited by side effects including tachycardia, anxiety, and tremor, which would be particularly problematic in a patient with Parkinson disease.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe management of orthostatic hypotension should always begin with non-pharmacological measures including compression stockings, adequate hydration, and avoiding rapid position changes. When these measures are insufficient, pharmacological therapy may be necessary, with the choice of agent guided by the patient\u0027s comorbidities and contraindications.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Fludrocortisone is first-line pharmacological therapy for orthostatic hypotension when non-pharmacological measures are insufficient.","Midodrine should be used cautiously in patients with Parkinson disease due to risk of worsening supine hypertension.","Non-pharmacological measures including compression stockings and adequate hydration are important initial steps in managing orthostatic hypotension."],"references":["Palma JA, Kaufmann H. Treatment of autonomic dysfunction in Parkinson disease and other synucleinopathies. Mov Disord. 2018;33(3):372-390. doi:10.1002/mds.27344. Available online at ; https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC5844369/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88299"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18970"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88299","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/88299"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-06-14T09:56:53+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-14T09:56:53+09:30","number":6,"notes":"fixed typo","plagiarismCheckedAt":null,"plagiarismScore":null,"plagiarismReportUrl":null},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11704"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"105830"}},"author":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"9435"}},"generation":{"data":null}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"6","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/6"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc75","name":"Geriatrics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"28","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/28"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc95","name":"Palliative Care","synonyms":null,"description":null